1484630775.text: "In the late stage of endoreduplication, the effects of PTX-2 on different cancer cells involves : (i) down-regulation of anti-apoptotic Bcl-2 members and IAP family proteins; (ii) up-regulation of pro apoptotic Bax protein and tumor necrosis factor related apoptosis inducing ligand (TRAIL)-receptor 1/receptor 2 (DR4 and DR5); and (iii) mitochondrial dysfunction."
